The paper deals with the problem of spatiotemporal saliency prediction in aerial videos using a crowdsourced multi-path network. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques for analyzing visual data, as well as robotics (RO) for the use of drones to capture aerial footage. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) techniques, which fall under the categories of multimedia (MM), artificial intelligence (AI), and machine learning (LG). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV, followed by cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.AI, and cs.LG.
